<HEADLINE>
Germany honored by Ratzinger becoming pope, says Schroeder
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BERLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder on Tuesday called the choice of Cardinal
Joseph Ratzinger as pope an "honor" for Germany.
</P>
<P>
Ratzinger's election is "a great honor for our whole country," Schroeder told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder said Ratzinger, who will be known as Pope Benedict XVI, was a renowned
theologian across the world, and said he looked forward to him attending World
Youth Day in Cologne, Germany, in August.
</P>
<P>
German President Horst Koehler added: "That a fellow countryman has become pope
fills us with a special joy in Germany _ and also a little pride."
</P>
